Vice President Mike Pence spoke with President Ashraf Ghani of Afghanistan to discuss the security situation in Afghanistan and the impact of President Trump's South Asia strategy on the Afghan National Defense and Security Forces' morale. They also discussed the Taliban's view of their battlefield capabilities. Pence commended the Afghans for their bravery and sacrifices in fighting the insurgency and international terrorists. He highlighted Kabul's engagement and progress on necessary reforms, political inclusion, and preparations for forthcoming elections, all of which are critical for stability and opportunities in Afghanistan. Pence and Ghani reaffirmed the enduring partnership between the United States and Afghanistan.